
[1]salacious

   SALA'CIOUS, a. [L. salax, from the root of sal, salt; the primary sense
   of which is shooting, penetrating, pungent, coinciding probably with L.
   salio, to leap. Salacious then is highly excited, or prompt to leap.]
   Lustful; lecherous.
